cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with gaze estimation, which is a computer vision problem, and specifically utilizes saliency information in the visual content. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also addresses the challenge of user calibration, which is related to human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a likely sub-category as well. The use of CNN-based models for optimization suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible sub-category. The paper also introduces a new algorithm for transforming saliency maps, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
